h3cDot11CFG.contactinfo: Platform Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip: 100085
h3cDot11CFG.description: This MIB provides information about WLAN configuration. GLOSSARY IEEE 802.11 Standard to encourage interoperability among wireless networking equipment. Access point (AP) Transmitter/receiver (transceiver) device that commonly connects and transports data between a wireless network and a wired network. Access control (AC) To control and manage multi-APs, it will bridge wireless and wired network. Fat AP Applied in the home, SOHO and so on, and it could work independently without help from AC. Fit AP Applied in the enterprise environment, it will work under the control and management from AC. Control And Provisioning of Wireless Access Points Protocol The short name of protocol is CAPWAP. AC will control and manage AP by CAPWAP tunnel protocol defined by IETF. Also, a data tunnel will be set up between AC and AP. BSS IEEE 802.11 Basic Service Set (Radio Cell). The BSS of an AP comprises of the stations directly associating with the AP. Radio The chip set to receive and send wireless signal. Association The service used to establish access point or station mapping and enable station invocation of the distribution system services. (Wireless clients attempt to connect to access points.) Basic Rate A data rate that is mandatory for client devices to support in order for them to achieve successful association. MSDU MAC Service Data Unit, it is frame format defined by 802.11. TU It is 1,024 microseconds (ms), which is about 1 millisecond. AKM The authentication and key management method defined by 802.11i, and which includes 802.1x and pre-shared key.

h3cDot11GlobalCountryCode.name: h3cDot11GlobalCountryCode
h3cDot11GlobalCountryCode.description: Represents the country code for wireless network.

h3cDot11StaKeepALiveTimerIntvl.name: h3cDot11StaKeepALiveTimerIntvl
h3cDot11StaKeepALiveTimerIntvl.description: Represents the interval of the keep alive requests sent between AP and STA. Default value 0 : The keep alive function is disabled.

h3cDot11StaIdleTimerIntvl.name: h3cDot11StaIdleTimerIntvl
h3cDot11StaIdleTimerIntvl.description: Represents the interval for which the link between AP and STA ( power-save or awake ) can be idle.

h3cDot11BroadcastProbeReply.name: h3cDot11BroadcastProbeReply
h3cDot11BroadcastProbeReply.description: Represents enable the AP to reply broadcast probe or not. 'true' : The AP to reply broadcast probe is enabled. 'false': The AP to reply broadcast probe is disabled

h3cDot11APScanMode.name: h3cDot11APScanMode
h3cDot11APScanMode.description: Represents the scanning mode for AP. The following values are supported: active(1), - AP will actively do scan. passive(2) - AP will passively do scan.

h3cDot11ACCtrlTunnelSecSupport.name: h3cDot11ACCtrlTunnelSecSupport
h3cDot11ACCtrlTunnelSecSupport.description: Represents what security schemes are supported for CAPWAP Control tunnel.

h3cDot11ACDataTunnelSecSupport.name: h3cDot11ACDataTunnelSecSupport
h3cDot11ACDataTunnelSecSupport.description: Represents what security schemes are supported for CAPWAP data tunnel. The cleartxt is the default scheme.

h3cDot11ACAutoAPSupport.name: h3cDot11ACAutoAPSupport
h3cDot11ACAutoAPSupport.description: Represents enable the auto AP functionality or not. 'true' : The auto AP functionality is enabled. 'false': The auto AP functionality is disabled

h3cDot11AutoAPName.name: h3cDot11AutoAPName
h3cDot11AutoAPName.description: Represents the name of auto AP which need to be made persistent. When read the value from the node, NULL value be returned.

h3cDot11PersistentName.name: h3cDot11PersistentName
h3cDot11PersistentName.description: Represents the new name of auto AP after being made persistent. When read the value from the node, NULL value be returned.

h3cDot11IntfTrapThreshold.name: h3cDot11IntfTrapThreshold
h3cDot11IntfTrapThreshold.description: Represents threshold of interference trap. If signal strength of the device exceeds this threshold, corresponding trap will be sent.

h3cDot11MonitorInterval.name: h3cDot11MonitorInterval
h3cDot11MonitorInterval.description: Represents the monitoring interval. Default value 0 : The monitoring functionality is changed to real-time mode.

h3cDot11SampleInterval.name: h3cDot11SampleInterval
h3cDot11SampleInterval.description: Represents the sampling interval. Default value 0 : The sampling functionality is disabled.

h3cDot11ChnlSwitChkInterval.name: h3cDot11ChnlSwitChkInterval
h3cDot11ChnlSwitChkInterval.description: Represents the checking interval of channel switch.

h3cDot11APUserUplimit.name: h3cDot11APUserUplimit
h3cDot11APUserUplimit.description: Represents the upper limit of user which has access to this AP.

h3cDot11APL2IsolateEnable.name: h3cDot11APL2IsolateEnable
h3cDot11APL2IsolateEnable.description: Represents enable the layer2 isolation or not. 'true' : The layer2 isolation functionality is enabled. 'false': The layer2 isolation functionality is disabled.

h3cDot11APBSSIDSupportNum.name: h3cDot11APBSSIDSupportNum
h3cDot11APBSSIDSupportNum.description: Represents the max number of BSSID supported by Current AP.

h3cDot11APLastUpdateStatTime.name: h3cDot11APLastUpdateStatTime
h3cDot11APLastUpdateStatTime.description: Represents date and time update statistic information lately.

h3cDot11APDoSProtectEnable.name: h3cDot11APDoSProtectEnable
h3cDot11APDoSProtectEnable.description: Represents enable the DOS protection or not. 'true' : The DOS protection functionality is enabled. 'false': The DOS protection functionality is disabled.

h3cDot11MaxAPPerIf.name: h3cDot11MaxAPPerIf
h3cDot11MaxAPPerIf.description: Represents max AP number that can be connected to AC interface.

h3cDot11SampleTimeStamp.name: h3cDot11SampleTimeStamp
h3cDot11SampleTimeStamp.description: Represents the start time of current sample period.

h3cDot11UplinkTrackId.name: h3cDot11UplinkTrackId
h3cDot11UplinkTrackId.description: Represents the track id of AP. Default value 0 : The uplink track function for AP is disabled.

h3cDot11RtCollectSwitch.name: h3cDot11RtCollectSwitch
h3cDot11RtCollectSwitch.description: This object is used to turn on/off real-time statistics collection between AC and AP. If the value is true, h3cDot11RtCollectIntvl will take effect. Otherwise, h3cDot11RglCollectIntvl will take effect.

h3cDot11RglCollectIntvl.name: h3cDot11RglCollectIntvl
h3cDot11RglCollectIntvl.description: This object represents interval to regularly collect statistics from AC to AP.

h3cDot11RtCollectIntvl.name: h3cDot11RtCollectIntvl
h3cDot11RtCollectIntvl.description: This object represents interval to collect real-time statistics from AC to AP.

h3cDot11AllAPCpuUsageThreshold.name: h3cDot11AllAPCpuUsageThreshold
h3cDot11AllAPCpuUsageThreshold.description: The CPU usage threshold for all AP.

h3cDot11AllAPMemUsageThreshold.name: h3cDot11AllAPMemUsageThreshold
h3cDot11AllAPMemUsageThreshold.description: The memory usage threshold for all AP.

h3cDot11AdjIntfTrapThreshold.name: h3cDot11AdjIntfTrapThreshold
h3cDot11AdjIntfTrapThreshold.description: Represents threshold of adjacent interference trap. If signal strength of the device exceeds this threshold, corresponding trap will be sent.

h3cDot11AllAPMonitorMode.name: h3cDot11AllAPMonitorMode
h3cDot11AllAPMonitorMode.description: Represents what work mode for All AP. The following values are supported: normal, - AP will supply WLAN service. monitor - AP will be a monitor to find attack. hybrid - AP will supply WLAN service and Device detection is enabled.

h3cDot11RadioPolicyTable.name: h3cDot11RadioPolicyTable
h3cDot11RadioPolicyTable.description: The table defines the parameters for radio policy, as per radio policy of CLI. One radio policy could be assigned to the different radios (AP).

h3cDot11RadioPolicyEntry.name: h3cDot11RadioPolicyEntry
h3cDot11RadioPolicyEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each radio policy.

h3cDot11RadioPolicyName.name: h3cDot11RadioPolicyName
h3cDot11RadioPolicyName.description: Represents the name of radio policy.

h3cDot11BeaconInterval.name: h3cDot11BeaconInterval
h3cDot11BeaconInterval.description: Represents the interval for Beacon management frame.

h3cDot11DtimInterval.name: h3cDot11DtimInterval
h3cDot11DtimInterval.description: Represents the number of beacon intervals that shall elapse between transmission of Beacons frames containing a Traffic Indication Map (TIM) element whose DTIM Count field is 0. This value is transmitted in the Delivery TIM (DTIM) Period field of Beacon frames.

h3cDot11RtsThreshold.name: h3cDot11RtsThreshold
h3cDot11RtsThreshold.description: Represents the current minimum size,in octets,of the MAC protocol data unit (MPDU), below which a Request to send/Clear to send (RTS/CTS) handshake shall not be performed.

h3cDot11FragThreshold.name: h3cDot11FragThreshold
h3cDot11FragThreshold.description: Represents the current maximum size, in octets, of the MPDU that may be delivered to the PHY. A MSDU shall be broken into fragments if its size exceeds the value of this attribute after adding MAC headers and trailers.

h3cDot11ShortRetryThreshold.name: h3cDot11ShortRetryThreshold
h3cDot11ShortRetryThreshold.description: Represents the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is less than or equal to h3cDot11RTSThreshold, that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated.

h3cDot11LongRetryThreshold.name: h3cDot11LongRetryThreshold
h3cDot11LongRetryThreshold.description: Represents the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is longer than h3cDot11RTSThreshold, that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated.

h3cDot11MaxRxLifetime.name: h3cDot11MaxRxLifetime
h3cDot11MaxRxLifetime.description: Represents the elapsed time. After the time specified by h3cDot11MaxRxLifetime, the further attempts to reassemble the MSDU shall be terminated.

h3cDot11RdoPolicyRowStatus.name: h3cDot11RdoPolicyRowStatus
h3cDot11RdoPolicyRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cDot11RdoClientMaxCount.name: h3cDot11RdoClientMaxCount
h3cDot11RdoClientMaxCount.description: Represent the maximum number of stations supported by this radio policy.

h3cDot11BeaconIntervalMs.name: h3cDot11BeaconIntervalMs
h3cDot11BeaconIntervalMs.description: Represents the interval for Beacon management frame.

h3cDot11ServicePolicyTable.name: h3cDot11ServicePolicyTable
h3cDot11ServicePolicyTable.description: The table defines the parameters for ESS, as per service policy of CLI. One service policy could be assigned to the different radios (AP).

h3cDot11ServicePolicyEntry.name: h3cDot11ServicePolicyEntry
h3cDot11ServicePolicyEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each service policy.

h3cDot11ServicePolicyID.name: h3cDot11ServicePolicyID
h3cDot11ServicePolicyID.description: Represents the ID of each service policy.

h3cDot11SSIDName.name: h3cDot11SSIDName
h3cDot11SSIDName.description: Represents the ESS. As per CLI, the value of service policy name will be SSID.

h3cDot11SSIDHidden.name: h3cDot11SSIDHidden
h3cDot11SSIDHidden.description: This attribute controls whether the SSID will be advertised in the beacon frame. If it is true, then SSID will not be advertised in the beacon frame.

h3cDot11AuthenMode.name: h3cDot11AuthenMode
h3cDot11AuthenMode.description: Represents the Authentication mode defined by 802.11.

h3cDot11SSIDEncryptionMode.name: h3cDot11SSIDEncryptionMode
h3cDot11SSIDEncryptionMode.description: Represents the encryption mode for this ESS.

h3cDot11WlanInfBindingType.name: h3cDot11WlanInfBindingType
h3cDot11WlanInfBindingType.description: Represents the service policy will bind to what kind of data forwarding interface.

h3cDot11WlanInfBindingID.name: h3cDot11WlanInfBindingID
h3cDot11WlanInfBindingID.description: Represents the interface ID of the interface that ESS will bind to. If the value is set to -1, the binding will be removed.

h3cDot11SrvPolicyRowStatus.name: h3cDot11SrvPolicyRowStatus
h3cDot11SrvPolicyRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cDot11ClientMaxCount.name: h3cDot11ClientMaxCount
h3cDot11ClientMaxCount.description: Represent the maximum number of stations supported by this service policy.

h3cDot11SPInCirMode.name: h3cDot11SPInCirMode
h3cDot11SPInCirMode.description: CIR(committed information rate) mode of inbound direction. This object is useful only when the corresponding CIR is nonzero. If value of this object is changed, corresponding CIR will be reset.

h3cDot11SPInCirValue.name: h3cDot11SPInCirValue
h3cDot11SPInCirValue.description: Represents the CIR of inbound direction of this service policy. If the value is 0, it means that no flow control is applied to the service policy, and the corresponding CIR mode is meaningless.

h3cDot11SPOutCirMode.name: h3cDot11SPOutCirMode
h3cDot11SPOutCirMode.description: CIR(committed information rate) mode of outbound direction. This object is useful only when the corresponding CIR is nonzero. If value of this object is changed, corresponding CIR will be reset.

h3cDot11SPOutCirValue.name: h3cDot11SPOutCirValue
h3cDot11SPOutCirValue.description: Represents the CIR of outbound direction of this service policy. If the value is 0, it means that no flow control is applied to the service policy, and the corresponding CIR mode is meaningless.

h3cDot11WlanInfPVID.name: h3cDot11WlanInfPVID
h3cDot11WlanInfPVID.description: Represents the VLAN ID of SSID.

h3cDot11SPInCirStaticValue.name: h3cDot11SPInCirStaticValue
h3cDot11SPInCirStaticValue.description: Represents the CIR of inbound direction for static CIR mode.

h3cDot11SPOutCirStaticValue.name: h3cDot11SPOutCirStaticValue
h3cDot11SPOutCirStaticValue.description: Represents the CIR of outbound direction for static CIR mode.

h3cDot11SPIsolate.name: h3cDot11SPIsolate
h3cDot11SPIsolate.description: If it is true, then stations connected with the service policy are isolated.

h3cDot11WAPIAuthServerIP.name: h3cDot11WAPIAuthServerIP
h3cDot11WAPIAuthServerIP.description: Represents the IP address of the WAPI Authentication server

h3cDot11ServicePolicyExtTable.name: h3cDot11ServicePolicyExtTable
h3cDot11ServicePolicyExtTable.description: The table defines the parameters for ESS, as per service policy of CLI. When the value of h3cDot11SSIDEncryptionMode equals to cipher(2), more configuration for a ESS will be put into the table.

h3cDot11ServicePolicyExtEntry.name: h3cDot11ServicePolicyExtEntry
h3cDot11ServicePolicyExtEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each service policy under cipher(2) mode.

h3cDot11ServicePolicyExtID.name: h3cDot11ServicePolicyExtID
h3cDot11ServicePolicyExtID.description: Represents the ID of each service policy.

h3cDot11SecIEStatus.name: h3cDot11SecIEStatus
h3cDot11SecIEStatus.description: To enable the security Information element in the beacon and probe response frames sent by AP.

h3cDot11SecurityCiphers.name: h3cDot11SecurityCiphers
h3cDot11SecurityCiphers.description: The WLAN system support the following cipher type for data frame encryption. wep40(2) tkip(4) aesccmp(16) wep104(32) wpisms4(64) wep128(128) For each service policy,it could support multiple cipher types at the same time.So the value of object could combine multiple value of cipher type above. When the value of node equals to zero, it means no configuration or undo operation.

h3cDot11CipherKeyIndex.name: h3cDot11CipherKeyIndex
h3cDot11CipherKeyIndex.description: Represents the key index of cipher key for packet. When h3cDot11SecurityCiphers value is wep40 or wep104, the configuration will take effective.

h3cDot11CipherKey.name: h3cDot11CipherKey
h3cDot11CipherKey.description: Represents the cipher key for packet. When h3cDot11SecurityCiphers value is wep40 or wep104, the configuration will take effective.

h3cDot11SrvPolicyExtRowStatus.name: h3cDot11SrvPolicyExtRowStatus
h3cDot11SrvPolicyExtRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cDot11CipherKeyType.name: h3cDot11CipherKeyType
h3cDot11CipherKeyType.description: Represents the cipher key type of h3cDot11CipherKey.

h3cDot11RadioPolicyExtTable.name: h3cDot11RadioPolicyExtTable
h3cDot11RadioPolicyExtTable.description: The table defines the radio policy of each radio. It can't be modified if the radio policy is a default radio policy.

h3cDot11RadioPolicyExtEntry.name: h3cDot11RadioPolicyExtEntry
h3cDot11RadioPolicyExtEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each radio policy.

h3cDot11RPAPSerialID.name: h3cDot11RPAPSerialID
h3cDot11RPAPSerialID.description: This object represents the Serial ID of AP.

h3cDot11RPBeaconInterval.name: h3cDot11RPBeaconInterval
h3cDot11RPBeaconInterval.description: This object represents the interval for Beacon management frame.

h3cDot11RPDtimInterval.name: h3cDot11RPDtimInterval
h3cDot11RPDtimInterval.description: This object represents the number of beacon intervals that shall elapse between transmissions of Beacons frames containing a Traffic Indication Map (TIM) element whose DTIM count field is 0. This value is transmitted in the Delivery TIM (DTIM) Period field of Beacon frames.

h3cDot11RPRtsThreshold.name: h3cDot11RPRtsThreshold
h3cDot11RPRtsThreshold.description: This object represents the current minimum size, in octets, of the MAC protocol data unit (MPDU), below which a Request to send/Clear to send (RTS/CTS) handshake shall not be performed.

h3cDot11RPFragThreshold.name: h3cDot11RPFragThreshold
h3cDot11RPFragThreshold.description: This object represents the current maximum size, in octets, of the MPDU that may be delivered to the PHY. A MSDU shall be broken into fragments if its size exceeds the value of this attribute after adding MAC headers and trailers.

h3cDot11RPShortRetryThreshold.name: h3cDot11RPShortRetryThreshold
h3cDot11RPShortRetryThreshold.description: This object represents the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is less than or equal to h3cDot11RTSThreshold, that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated.

h3cDot11RPLongRetryThreshold.name: h3cDot11RPLongRetryThreshold
h3cDot11RPLongRetryThreshold.description: This object represents the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is longer than h3cDot11RTSThreshold, and that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated.

h3cDot11RPClientMaxCount.name: h3cDot11RPClientMaxCount
h3cDot11RPClientMaxCount.description: This object represents the maximum number of stations supported by this radio policy.

h3cDot11SrvPortSecurityTable.name: h3cDot11SrvPortSecurityTable
h3cDot11SrvPortSecurityTable.description: This table defines the WLAN security status for ESS, BSS and WLAN-Ethernet interface which binding the crypto service-template. Otherwise, when binding the clear service-template, h3cPortSecurityTables should be used to configure port security.

h3cDot11SrvPortSecurityEntry.name: h3cDot11SrvPortSecurityEntry
h3cDot11SrvPortSecurityEntry.description: There is a row in this table for service policy.

h3cDot11SecurityServicePolicyID.name: h3cDot11SecurityServicePolicyID
h3cDot11SecurityServicePolicyID.description: Represents the ID of each service policy.

h3cDot11SrvPortSecurityMode.name: h3cDot11SrvPortSecurityMode
h3cDot11SrvPortSecurityMode.description: Determines the security modes of the WLAN port. noRestrictions(1) The default value,no any security mode is set. userLoginSecureExt(2) Access to the port is denied until the port client is authorized (by 802.1X). psk(3) Access to the port is denied until the port client is authorized (by 802.1X key negotiation). macAddressAndPsk(4) The MAC address is first authenticated and only if this succeeds does the psk then attempt user authentication. userLoginSecureExtOrPsk(5) This selects both the userLoginSecureExt and psk modes together such that either is allowed to authorized access. Which mode works for client depends on the client's choice. ext(6) Access to the port is denied until the port client is authenticated (by ext).

h3cDot11SrvSecurityKeyType.name: h3cDot11SrvSecurityKeyType
h3cDot11SrvSecurityKeyType.description: This indicates the key type in the 802.1X EAPOL_Key packet. userLoginTxKeyTypeNone(1) This means the key type is not set yet. userLoginTxKeyTypeDot11Key(2) This selects the 802.11 key type. userLoginTxKeyTypeRsaRC4Key(3) This selects the RC4 key for RSA RC4 session encryption.

h3cDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyMode.name: h3cDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyMode
h3cDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyMode.description: This is the password input mode. When input as pskKeyModePassPhrase, h3cDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyString must be 8 to 63 characters; when input as pskKeyModeRawKey, h3cDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyString must be 64 characters and each character must be '0'-'9', 'a'-'f' and 'A'-'F'.

h3cDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyString.name: h3cDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyString
h3cDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyString.description: This is the password string used for psk authentication.

h3cDot11SrvPolicyExtendTable.name: h3cDot11SrvPolicyExtendTable
h3cDot11SrvPolicyExtendTable.description: The table defines the parameters of each service policy.

h3cDot11SrvPolicyExtendEntry.name: h3cDot11SrvPolicyExtendEntry
h3cDot11SrvPolicyExtendEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each service policy.

h3cDot11SPEnable.name: h3cDot11SPEnable
h3cDot11SPEnable.description: Represents whether the service policy is enabled.

h3cDot11APTemplateTable.name: h3cDot11APTemplateTable
h3cDot11APTemplateTable.description: By AP template CLI, administrator will configure the parameters of AP by convenience. Before AP boot up and connect to AC by CAPWAP tunnel, administrator will create AP template for each AP. When AP connect to AC, AC will assign configuration to AP by h3cDot11APSerialID information in AP template.

h3cDot11APTemplateEntry.name: h3cDot11APTemplateEntry
h3cDot11APTemplateEntry.description: Each entry contains configuration information for each AP.

h3cDot11APTemplateName.name: h3cDot11APTemplateName
h3cDot11APTemplateName.description: Represents the name of AP template.

h3cDot11TemplateAPModelAlias.name: h3cDot11TemplateAPModelAlias
h3cDot11TemplateAPModelAlias.description: Represents the alias of AP model name.

h3cDot11Description.name: h3cDot11Description
h3cDot11Description.description: This attribute will give more information about AP. Administrator could suggest the location, owner or other information for each AP. If the value is set to NULL, the description will be removed.

h3cDot11APWorkMode.name: h3cDot11APWorkMode
h3cDot11APWorkMode.description: Represents what work mode for AP. The following values are supported: normal - AP will supply WLAN service. monitor - AP will be a monitor to find attack. hybrid - AP will supply WLAN service and Device detection is enabled.

h3cDot11APTemplateRowStatus.name: h3cDot11APTemplateRowStatus
h3cDot11APTemplateRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cDot11StatisInterv.name: h3cDot11StatisInterv
h3cDot11StatisInterv.description: Represents the interval of radio statistic.

h3cDot11APBroadcastProbeReply.name: h3cDot11APBroadcastProbeReply
h3cDot11APBroadcastProbeReply.description: Represents enable the AP to reply broadcast probe or not. 'true' : The AP to reply broadcast probe is enabled. 'false': The AP to reply broadcast probe is disabled

h3cDot11StaIdleTimerInterv.name: h3cDot11StaIdleTimerInterv
h3cDot11StaIdleTimerInterv.description: Represents the interval for which the link between AP and STA ( power-save or awake ) can be idle.

h3cDot11StaKeepAliveTimerInterv.name: h3cDot11StaKeepAliveTimerInterv
h3cDot11StaKeepAliveTimerInterv.description: Represents the interval of the keep alive requests sent between AP and STA.

h3cDot11APCir.name: h3cDot11APCir
h3cDot11APCir.description: Represents the committed information rate between AP and AC.

h3cDot11APCbs.name: h3cDot11APCbs
h3cDot11APCbs.description: Represents the committed burst size between AP and AC.

h3cDot11APPriorityLevel.name: h3cDot11APPriorityLevel
h3cDot11APPriorityLevel.description: This object represents the connection priority for the AP. If the connection priority is 7, the AC is considered as the primary AC for the AP.

h3cDot11APElementID.name: h3cDot11APElementID
h3cDot11APElementID.description: This object represents the AP element ID.

h3cDot11APDevDetectEnable.name: h3cDot11APDevDetectEnable
h3cDot11APDevDetectEnable.description: Represents whether device detection is enabled or not. 'true' : Device detection is enabled. 'false': Device detection is disabled. If device detection is enabled, the AP will provide both device detection and WLAN data services. By default, the AP only provides WLAN data services. When an AP works in monitor mode, that is, the value of object h3cDot11APWorkMode is monitor, device detection can not be enabled with object h3cDot11APDevDetectEnable.

h3cDot11APGetIPMethod.name: h3cDot11APGetIPMethod
h3cDot11APGetIPMethod.description: This object represents the method how AP gets IP address.

h3cDot11StatisIntervMode.name: h3cDot11StatisIntervMode
h3cDot11StatisIntervMode.description: This object represents the mode of statics interval. normal - statics interval value between 10s to 120s realtime - statics interval value between 2s to 5s

h3cDot11ApTrapEnabled.name: h3cDot11ApTrapEnabled
h3cDot11ApTrapEnabled.description: Represents whether the trap status is enabled or not. 'true' : Enable the trap status; 'false' : Disable the trap status.

h3cDot11RadioToConfigTable.name: h3cDot11RadioToConfigTable
h3cDot11RadioToConfigTable.description: Before AP connects to AC, administrator will configure radio parameter to each radio.

h3cDot11RadioToConfigEntry.name: h3cDot11RadioToConfigEntry
h3cDot11RadioToConfigEntry.description: Each entry contains configuration information for each radio.

h3cDot11APTemplateNameCfg.name: h3cDot11APTemplateNameCfg
h3cDot11APTemplateNameCfg.description: Represents the name of AP template.

h3cDot11CfgRadioPolicyName.name: h3cDot11CfgRadioPolicyName
h3cDot11CfgRadioPolicyName.description: Represents the name of radio policy.

h3cDot11CfgRadioType.name: h3cDot11CfgRadioType
h3cDot11CfgRadioType.description: Represents the radio will work with which 802.11 radio type.

h3cDot11CfgChannel.name: h3cDot11CfgChannel
h3cDot11CfgChannel.description: Represents the channel allocation of radio.

h3cDot11CfgMaxTxPowerLevel.name: h3cDot11CfgMaxTxPowerLevel
h3cDot11CfgMaxTxPowerLevel.description: Represents the maximal transmit power scope for AP.

h3cDot11PreambleLen.name: h3cDot11PreambleLen
h3cDot11PreambleLen.description: Represents whether use long or short preamble for 802.11 MAC frame. When h3cDot11CfgRadioType is either dot11b or dot11g, then value for h3cDot11PreambleLen will be valid. Othwise, the value for it will be invalid.

h3cDot11CfgRadioStatus.name: h3cDot11CfgRadioStatus
h3cDot11CfgRadioStatus.description: Represents the radio admin status whether is enabled or disabled.

h3cDot11CfgRdElementID.name: h3cDot11CfgRdElementID
h3cDot11CfgRdElementID.description: Represents the element ID of this radio. It comprises two parts. The highest 24 bits are AP element ID and the lowest 8 bits are radio ID.

h3cDot11CfgWorkMode.name: h3cDot11CfgWorkMode
h3cDot11CfgWorkMode.description: Represents work mode of the radio.

h3cDot11CfgPwrAttValue.name: h3cDot11CfgPwrAttValue
h3cDot11CfgPwrAttValue.description: Represents the value of power attenuation.

h3cDot11RadioTxArithmetic.name: h3cDot11RadioTxArithmetic
h3cDot11RadioTxArithmetic.description: Represents the transmission arithmetic of the radio. The following values are supported: quality(1) - Consider the quality first during the transmission. bandwidth(2) - Consider the bandwidth first during the transmission.

h3cDot11CfgChannelLockStat.name: h3cDot11CfgChannelLockStat
h3cDot11CfgChannelLockStat.description: Represents locked status of channel on the radio.

h3cDot11CfgPowerLockStat.name: h3cDot11CfgPowerLockStat
h3cDot11CfgPowerLockStat.description: Represents locked status of power on the radio.

h3cDot11CfgLBRdGroupId.name: h3cDot11CfgLBRdGroupId
h3cDot11CfgLBRdGroupId.description: Represents the load balance group ID allocated for the radio.

h3cDot11CfgRRMSDRdGroupId.name: h3cDot11CfgRRMSDRdGroupId
h3cDot11CfgRRMSDRdGroupId.description: Represents the RRM self-decisive group ID allocated for the radio.

h3cDot11CfgRadioType2.name: h3cDot11CfgRadioType2
h3cDot11CfgRadioType2.description: Represents the radio will work with which 802.11 radio type.

h3cDot11CfgIDSEnable.name: h3cDot11CfgIDSEnable
h3cDot11CfgIDSEnable.description: Represents whether intrusion detection is enabled for this radio.

h3cDot11CfgSaEnable.name: h3cDot11CfgSaEnable
h3cDot11CfgSaEnable.description: Represents whether spectrum analysis is enabled.

h3cDot11CfgSaCltRtFFTData.name: h3cDot11CfgSaCltRtFFTData
h3cDot11CfgSaCltRtFFTData.description: Represents whether to collect real-time FFT data for this radio.

h3cDot11CfgSaBand.name: h3cDot11CfgSaBand
h3cDot11CfgSaBand.description: Represents which band of channels will be monitored when collection real-time FFT data is enabled for this radio. Detection of interference devices and air quality will also be affected. Each band responds to the following channels. dot11g (Channels 1-14) dot11aLower (channels 36-64) dot11aMiddle (channels 100-140) dot11aUpper (channels 149-165).

h3cDot11APServiceSetTable.name: h3cDot11APServiceSetTable
h3cDot11APServiceSetTable.description: For each radio, it could configure multiple service policies. The table describes the relationship between radio and service policies.

h3cDot11APServiceSetEntry.name: h3cDot11APServiceSetEntry
h3cDot11APServiceSetEntry.description: Each entry contains service policy information for each specific radio of AP.

h3cDot11CfgServicePolicyID.name: h3cDot11CfgServicePolicyID
h3cDot11CfgServicePolicyID.description: Represents the ID of each service policy used by the AP.

h3cDot11SrvSetRowStatus.name: h3cDot11SrvSetRowStatus
h3cDot11SrvSetRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cDot11ServiceSetVlanId.name: h3cDot11ServiceSetVlanId
h3cDot11ServiceSetVlanId.description: Represents the Vlan ID of BSS which is generated when service policy is binded with the Radio.

h3cDot11APSTVlanTable.name: h3cDot11APSTVlanTable
h3cDot11APSTVlanTable.description: For each service policy, it could be bind to several VLANs. The table describes the relationship between VLAN and service policies.

h3cDot11APSTVlanEntry.name: h3cDot11APSTVlanEntry
h3cDot11APSTVlanEntry.description: Each entry contains VLAN and service policy information for each specific radio of AP.

h3cDot11CfgSTVLANID.name: h3cDot11CfgSTVLANID
h3cDot11CfgSTVLANID.description: Represents the VLAN that current Service Policy have bind to.

h3cDot11CfgSTNASPortID.name: h3cDot11CfgSTNASPortID
h3cDot11CfgSTNASPortID.description: Represents the NAS Port ID of current Service Policy for each specific radio of AP.

h3cDot11CfgServiceSetRowStatus.name: h3cDot11CfgServiceSetRowStatus
h3cDot11CfgServiceSetRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cDot11APSysInfoSetTable.name: h3cDot11APSysInfoSetTable
h3cDot11APSysInfoSetTable.description: The table of the system information for each AP.

h3cDot11APSysInfoSetEntry.name: h3cDot11APSysInfoSetEntry
h3cDot11APSysInfoSetEntry.description: The system information configuration for each AP.

h3cDot11APSysNetID.name: h3cDot11APSysNetID
h3cDot11APSysNetID.description: Represents the system Net ID for AP.

h3cDot11APCpuUsageThreshold.name: h3cDot11APCpuUsageThreshold
h3cDot11APCpuUsageThreshold.description: The CPU usage threshold for AP.

h3cDot11APMemUsageThreshold.name: h3cDot11APMemUsageThreshold
h3cDot11APMemUsageThreshold.description: The memory usage threshold for AP.

h3cDot11APLimitTable.name: h3cDot11APLimitTable
h3cDot11APLimitTable.description: For each connected APs, administrator could configure a series of limits. This table describes the limit information for AP(s).

h3cDot11APLimitEntry.name: h3cDot11APLimitEntry
h3cDot11APLimitEntry.description: Each entry contains the limit information for each AP.

h3cDot11APSsidNumLimit.name: h3cDot11APSsidNumLimit
h3cDot11APSsidNumLimit.description: Represents the upper limit of service template binded with this AP. All radios of AP share this limit. Default value 0 : There is no upper limit of service template binded with this AP.

h3cDot11APUserCntLimit.name: h3cDot11APUserCntLimit
h3cDot11APUserCntLimit.description: Represents the upper limit of user which has access to this AP. All BSSs binded with AP share this limit. Default value 0 : There is no upper limit of user which has access to this AP.

h3cDot11APUserThreshold.name: h3cDot11APUserThreshold
h3cDot11APUserThreshold.description: Represents the threshold of user which has access to this AP. All BSSs binded with AP share this limit. If the user counter is overflow, the trap will be sent. Default value 0 : There is no threshold of user which has access to this AP.

h3cDot11APIfSetTable.name: h3cDot11APIfSetTable
h3cDot11APIfSetTable.description: The table of the interface information for each AP.

h3cDot11APIfSetEntry.name: h3cDot11APIfSetEntry
h3cDot11APIfSetEntry.description: The interface information configuration for each AP.

h3cDot11APSetIfIndex.name: h3cDot11APSetIfIndex
h3cDot11APSetIfIndex.description: Represents the index for a interface.

h3cDot11APIfAlias.name: h3cDot11APIfAlias
h3cDot11APIfAlias.description: This object is an 'alias' name for the interface as specified by a network manager for AP.

h3cDot11APServiceVlanTable.name: h3cDot11APServiceVlanTable
h3cDot11APServiceVlanTable.description: For all the radios on the AP, it could configure multiple service policies. The table describes the relationship between AP and service policies.

h3cDot11APServiceVlanEntry.name: h3cDot11APServiceVlanEntry
h3cDot11APServiceVlanEntry.description: Each entry contains service policy information for each AP.

h3cDot11APServiceVlanSerialID.name: h3cDot11APServiceVlanSerialID
h3cDot11APServiceVlanSerialID.description: This object represents AP serial id.

h3cDot11APServiceVlanSPID.name: h3cDot11APServiceVlanSPID
h3cDot11APServiceVlanSPID.description: This object represents the ID of each service policy used by the AP.

h3cDot11APServiceVlanId.name: h3cDot11APServiceVlanId
h3cDot11APServiceVlanId.description: This object represents the VLAN ID of BSS which is generated when the service policy is bound to the radio.

h3cDot11APServiceVlanRowStatus.name: h3cDot11APServiceVlanRowStatus
h3cDot11APServiceVlanRowStatus.description: This object represents the status of this table entry.

h3cDot11RadioConfigTable.name: h3cDot11RadioConfigTable
h3cDot11RadioConfigTable.description: Before AP connects to AC, administrator will configure radio parameter to each radio.

h3cDot11RadioConfigEntry.name: h3cDot11RadioConfigEntry
h3cDot11RadioConfigEntry.description: Each entry contains configuration information for each radio.

h3cDot11RCAPSerialID.name: h3cDot11RCAPSerialID
h3cDot11RCAPSerialID.description: This object represents the Serial ID of AP.

h3cDot11RCRadioType.name: h3cDot11RCRadioType
h3cDot11RCRadioType.description: This object represents the radio will work with which 802.11 radio type.

h3cDot11RCChannel.name: h3cDot11RCChannel
h3cDot11RCChannel.description: This object represents the channel allocation of radio.

h3cDot11RCPreambleLen.name: h3cDot11RCPreambleLen
h3cDot11RCPreambleLen.description: This object represents whether use long or short preamble for 802.11 MAC frame. When h3cDot11CfgRadioType is either dot11b or dot11g, then value for h3cDot11PreambleLen will be valid. Otherwise, the value for it will be invalid.

h3cDot11RCPwrAttValue.name: h3cDot11RCPwrAttValue
h3cDot11RCPwrAttValue.description: This object represents the value of power attenuation.

h3cDot11RCApPowerLevel.name: h3cDot11RCApPowerLevel
h3cDot11RCApPowerLevel.description: Represents the maximal transmit power scope for AP.

h3cDot11RCDynamicPowerState.name: h3cDot11RCDynamicPowerState
h3cDot11RCDynamicPowerState.description: Enable/Disable dynamic power selection for the band.

h3cDot11RCRadioStatus.name: h3cDot11RCRadioStatus
h3cDot11RCRadioStatus.description: Represents the radio admin status whether is enabled or disabled.

h3cDot11RCRadioRate.name: h3cDot11RCRadioRate
h3cDot11RCRadioRate.description: Set data transmit rates for the radio, in the format of 1,2,5.5... For 802.11n radios, the format can be MCS X. The data transmit rates between AP and STA must fall into the configured rates. (Note: For 802.11n radios, the first value will be treated as a mandatory rate, and the second value will be treated as a supported rate. If you configure more than two rates, the configuration cannot take effect. If you configure only one rate, it is considered as the mandatory rate by default.)

h3cDot11RCRadioType2.name: h3cDot11RCRadioType2
h3cDot11RCRadioType2.description: This object represents the radio will work with which 802.11 radio type.

h3cDot11RadioSSIDCfgTable.name: h3cDot11RadioSSIDCfgTable
h3cDot11RadioSSIDCfgTable.description: For each radio, it could configure multiple service policies. The table describes the relationship between radio and service policies.

h3cDot11RadioSSIDCfgEntry.name: h3cDot11RadioSSIDCfgEntry
h3cDot11RadioSSIDCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains SSID configuration information for each radio.

h3cDot11RadioSSIDSerialID.name: h3cDot11RadioSSIDSerialID
h3cDot11RadioSSIDSerialID.description: This object represents the serial ID of AP.

h3cDot11RadioSSIDWLANID.name: h3cDot11RadioSSIDWLANID
h3cDot11RadioSSIDWLANID.description: This object represents the WLAN ID of the BSSID.

h3cDot11RadioSSIDIndex.name: h3cDot11RadioSSIDIndex
h3cDot11RadioSSIDIndex.description: This object represents the ID of each service policy used by the radio.

h3cDot11RadioBSSID.name: h3cDot11RadioBSSID
h3cDot11RadioBSSID.description: As MAC address format, it is used to identify BSS.

h3cDot11APSerialIDTable.name: h3cDot11APSerialIDTable
h3cDot11APSerialIDTable.description: The table will provide the general information about APs.

h3cDot11APSerialIDEntry.name: h3cDot11APSerialIDEntry
h3cDot11APSerialIDEntry.description: Each entry contains the general information of an AP.

h3cDot11SIDAPWorkMode.name: h3cDot11SIDAPWorkMode
h3cDot11SIDAPWorkMode.description: Represents what work mode for AP. The following values are supported: normal - AP will supply WLAN service. monitor - AP will be a monitor to find attack. hybrid - AP will supply WLAN service and Device detection is enabled.

h3cDot11SIDAPGetIPMethod.name: h3cDot11SIDAPGetIPMethod
h3cDot11SIDAPGetIPMethod.description: This object represents the method how AP gets IP address.

h3cDot11SIDAPTemplateName.name: h3cDot11SIDAPTemplateName
h3cDot11SIDAPTemplateName.description: Represents the name of AP template.

h3cDot11SIDModelAlias.name: h3cDot11SIDModelAlias
h3cDot11SIDModelAlias.description: Represents the alias of AP model name.

h3cDot11SIDAPDescription.name: h3cDot11SIDAPDescription
h3cDot11SIDAPDescription.description: This attribute will give more information about AP. Administrator could suggest the location, owner or other information for each AP. If the value is set to NULL, the description will be removed.

h3cDot11SIDRowStatus.name: h3cDot11SIDRowStatus
h3cDot11SIDRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cDot11SIDStatisInterv.name: h3cDot11SIDStatisInterv
h3cDot11SIDStatisInterv.description: Represents the interval of radio statistic.

h3cDot11SIDAPBroadcastProbeReply.name: h3cDot11SIDAPBroadcastProbeReply
h3cDot11SIDAPBroadcastProbeReply.description: Represents enable the AP to reply broadcast probe or not. 'true' : The AP to reply broadcast probe is enabled. 'false': The AP to reply broadcast probe is disabled

h3cDot11SIDAPStaIdleTimerInterv.name: h3cDot11SIDAPStaIdleTimerInterv
h3cDot11SIDAPStaIdleTimerInterv.description: Represents the interval for which the link between AP and STA ( power-save or awake ) can be idle.

h3cDot11SIDStaKeepAliveTimerInterv.name: h3cDot11SIDStaKeepAliveTimerInterv
h3cDot11SIDStaKeepAliveTimerInterv.description: Represents the interval of the keep alive requests sent between AP and STA.

h3cDot11SIDAPCir.name: h3cDot11SIDAPCir
h3cDot11SIDAPCir.description: Represents the committed information rate between AP and AC.

h3cDot11SIDAPCbs.name: h3cDot11SIDAPCbs
h3cDot11SIDAPCbs.description: Represents the committed burst size between AP and AC.

h3cDot11SIDAPPriorityLevel.name: h3cDot11SIDAPPriorityLevel
h3cDot11SIDAPPriorityLevel.description: This object represents the connection priority for the AP. If the connection priority is 7, the AC is considered as the primary AC for the AP.

h3cDot11SIDAPElementID.name: h3cDot11SIDAPElementID
h3cDot11SIDAPElementID.description: This object represents the AP element ID.

h3cDot11SIDAPDevDetectEnable.name: h3cDot11SIDAPDevDetectEnable
h3cDot11SIDAPDevDetectEnable.description: Represents whether device detection is enabled or not. 'true' : Device detection is enabled. 'false': Device detection is disabled. If device detection is enabled, the AP will provide both device detection and WLAN data services. By default, the AP only provides WLAN data services. When an AP works in monitor mode, that is, the value of object h3cDot11APWorkMode is monitor, device detection can not be enabled with object h3cDot11SIDAPDevDetectEnable.

h3cDot11SIDAPStatisIntervMode.name: h3cDot11SIDAPStatisIntervMode
h3cDot11SIDAPStatisIntervMode.description: This object represents the mode of statics interval. normal - statics interval value between 10s to 120s realtime - statics interval value between 2s to 5s

h3cDot11RadioIntfConfigTable.name: h3cDot11RadioIntfConfigTable
h3cDot11RadioIntfConfigTable.description: The table defines the parameters for radio in AP, as per radio.

h3cDot11RadioIntfConfigEntry.name: h3cDot11RadioIntfConfigEntry
h3cDot11RadioIntfConfigEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each radio in AP.

h3cDot11RadioIfIdx.name: h3cDot11RadioIfIdx
h3cDot11RadioIfIdx.description: Represents the Radio IfIndex of radio in AP.

h3cDot11RadioCfgBeaconIntvl.name: h3cDot11RadioCfgBeaconIntvl
h3cDot11RadioCfgBeaconIntvl.description: Represents the interval for Beacon management frame.

h3cDot11RadioCfgDtimIntvl.name: h3cDot11RadioCfgDtimIntvl
h3cDot11RadioCfgDtimIntvl.description: Represents the number of beacon intervals that shall elapse between transmission of Beacons frames containing a Traffic Indication Map (TIM) element whose DTIM Count field is 0. This value is transmitted in the Delivery TIM (DTIM) Period field of Beacon frames.

h3cDot11RadioCfgRtsThreshold.name: h3cDot11RadioCfgRtsThreshold
h3cDot11RadioCfgRtsThreshold.description: Represents the current minimum size,in octets,of the MAC protocol data unit (MPDU), below which a Request to send/Clear to send (RTS/CTS) handshake shall not be performed.

h3cDot11RadioCfgFragThreshold.name: h3cDot11RadioCfgFragThreshold
h3cDot11RadioCfgFragThreshold.description: Represents the current maximum size, in octets, of the MPDU that may be delivered to the PHY. A MSDU shall be broken into fragments if its size exceeds the value of this attribute after adding MAC headers and trailers.

h3cDot11RadioCfgShtRetryThld.name: h3cDot11RadioCfgShtRetryThld
h3cDot11RadioCfgShtRetryThld.description: Represents the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is less than or equal to h3cDot11RadioRTSThreshold, that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated.

h3cDot11RadioCfglongRtrThld.name: h3cDot11RadioCfglongRtrThld
h3cDot11RadioCfglongRtrThld.description: Represents the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is longer than h3cDot11RadioRTSThreshold, that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated.

h3cDot11RadioCfgMaxRxLifetime.name: h3cDot11RadioCfgMaxRxLifetime
h3cDot11RadioCfgMaxRxLifetime.description: Represents the elapsed time. After the time specified by h3cDot11RadioCfgMaxRxLifetime, the further attempts to reassemble the MSDU shall be terminated.

h3cDot11RadioCfgType.name: h3cDot11RadioCfgType
h3cDot11RadioCfgType.description: Represents the radio will work with which 802.11 radio type.

h3cDot11RadioCfgChannel.name: h3cDot11RadioCfgChannel
h3cDot11RadioCfgChannel.description: Represents the channel allocation of radio.

h3cDot11RadioCfgMaxTxPwrLvl.name: h3cDot11RadioCfgMaxTxPwrLvl
h3cDot11RadioCfgMaxTxPwrLvl.description: Represents the maximal transmit power scope for AP.

h3cDot11RadioCfgPreambleLen.name: h3cDot11RadioCfgPreambleLen
h3cDot11RadioCfgPreambleLen.description: Represents whether use long or short preamble for 802.11 MAC frame.

h3cDot11RadioCfgWorkMode.name: h3cDot11RadioCfgWorkMode
h3cDot11RadioCfgWorkMode.description: Represents work mode of the radio.

h3cDot11RadioCfgOnly11gEnable.name: h3cDot11RadioCfgOnly11gEnable
h3cDot11RadioCfgOnly11gEnable.description: Represents whether enable only 802.11g radio mode or not. 'true' : Only 802.11g radio mode is enabled. 'false': Only 802.11g radio mode is disabled.

h3cDot11RadioCfgType2.name: h3cDot11RadioCfgType2
h3cDot11RadioCfgType2.description: Represents the radio will work with which 802.11 radio type.

h3cDot11RadioIntfBindTable.name: h3cDot11RadioIntfBindTable
h3cDot11RadioIntfBindTable.description: The table defines the binding information for each radio in AP.

h3cDot11RadioIntfBindEntry.name: h3cDot11RadioIntfBindEntry
h3cDot11RadioIntfBindEntry.description: Each entry contains the radio interface binding information in AP.

h3cDot11RadioIntfBindSvcPlcyID.name: h3cDot11RadioIntfBindSvcPlcyID
h3cDot11RadioIntfBindSvcPlcyID.description: Represents the ID of each service policy.

h3cDot11RadioIntfBindIfIdx.name: h3cDot11RadioIntfBindIfIdx
h3cDot11RadioIntfBindIfIdx.description: Represents the Ifindex of interface which is binded to the radio.

h3cDot11RadioIntfBindRowStatus.name: h3cDot11RadioIntfBindRowStatus
h3cDot11RadioIntfBindRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

h3cDot11DataRateConfigTable.name: h3cDot11DataRateConfigTable
h3cDot11DataRateConfigTable.description: Table will provide data rate configuration for a specific radio type.

h3cDot11DataRateConfigEntry.name: h3cDot11DataRateConfigEntry
h3cDot11DataRateConfigEntry.description: Each entry of the table will provide data rate configuration for a specific radio type.

h3cDot11SupportedRateSet.name: h3cDot11SupportedRateSet
h3cDot11SupportedRateSet.description: Represents the supported rate set of a particular radio type.

h3cDot11MandatoryRateSet.name: h3cDot11MandatoryRateSet
h3cDot11MandatoryRateSet.description: Represents the mandatory rate set of a particular radio type.

h3cDot11DisabledRateSet.name: h3cDot11DisabledRateSet
h3cDot11DisabledRateSet.description: Represents the disabled rate set of a particular radio type.

h3cDot11SmartRateSet.name: h3cDot11SmartRateSet
h3cDot11SmartRateSet.description: Represents the rate set of a particular radio type.

h3cDot11WlanEssIfTable.name: h3cDot11WlanEssIfTable
h3cDot11WlanEssIfTable.description: This table is used to configure WLAN ESS interface.

h3cDot11WlanEssIfEntry.name: h3cDot11WlanEssIfEntry
h3cDot11WlanEssIfEntry.description: Each entry contains the WLAN ESS interface configuration.

h3cDot11WlanEssIfNumber.name: h3cDot11WlanEssIfNumber
h3cDot11WlanEssIfNumber.description: This node represents the WLAN ESS interface number.

h3cDot11WlanEssIfIndex.name: h3cDot11WlanEssIfIndex
h3cDot11WlanEssIfIndex.description: This node represents the ifIndex of WLAN-ESS interface.

h3cDot11WlanEssRowStatus.name: h3cDot11WlanEssRowStatus
h3cDot11WlanEssRowStatus.description: This node represents the WLAN ESS interface row status.

h3cDot11WlanBssIfTable.name: h3cDot11WlanBssIfTable
h3cDot11WlanBssIfTable.description: This table is used to configure WLAN BSS interface.

h3cDot11WlanBssIfEntry.name: h3cDot11WlanBssIfEntry
h3cDot11WlanBssIfEntry.description: Each entry contains the WLAN BSS interface configuration.

h3cDot11WlanBssIfNumber.name: h3cDot11WlanBssIfNumber
h3cDot11WlanBssIfNumber.description: This node represents the WLAN BSS interface number.

h3cDot11WlanBssIfIndex.name: h3cDot11WlanBssIfIndex
h3cDot11WlanBssIfIndex.description: This node represents the ifIndex of WLAN-BSS interface.

h3cDot11WlanBssRowStatus.name: h3cDot11WlanBssRowStatus
h3cDot11WlanBssRowStatus.description: This node represents the WLAN BSS interface row status.

h3cDot11WLANEthernetIfTable.name: h3cDot11WLANEthernetIfTable
h3cDot11WLANEthernetIfTable.description: This table is used to configure WLAN Ethernet interface.

h3cDot11WLANEthernetIfEntry.name: h3cDot11WLANEthernetIfEntry
h3cDot11WLANEthernetIfEntry.description: Each entry contains the WLAN Ethernet interface configuration.

h3cDot11WlanEthernetIfNumber.name: h3cDot11WlanEthernetIfNumber
h3cDot11WlanEthernetIfNumber.description: This node represents the WLAN Ethernet interface number.

h3cDot11WLANEthernetIfIndex.name: h3cDot11WLANEthernetIfIndex
h3cDot11WLANEthernetIfIndex.description: This node represents the ifIndex of WLAN-Ethernet interface.

h3cDot11WlanEthernetRowStatus.name: h3cDot11WlanEthernetRowStatus
h3cDot11WlanEthernetRowStatus.description: This node represents the Wlan Ethernet interface row status.

h3cDot11PortSecurityTable.name: h3cDot11PortSecurityTable
h3cDot11PortSecurityTable.description: This table defines the WLAN security status for ESS, BSS, mesh and WLAN-Ethernet interface which binding the crypto service-template. Otherwise, when binding the clear service-template, h3cPortSecurityTables should be used to configure port security.

h3cDot11PortSecurityEntry.name: h3cDot11PortSecurityEntry
h3cDot11PortSecurityEntry.description: There is a row in this table for each ESS, BSS and WLAN-Ethernet interface.It is indexed using the object ifIndex in RFC1213-MIB.

h3cDot11PortSecurityMode.name: h3cDot11PortSecurityMode
h3cDot11PortSecurityMode.description: Determines the security modes of the WLAN port. noRestrictions(1) The default value,no any security mode is set. userLoginSecureExt(2) Access to the port is denied until the port client is authorized (by 802.1X). psk(3) Access to the port is denied until the port client is authorized (by 802.1X key negotiation). macAddressAndPsk(4) The MAC address is first authenticated and only if this succeeds does the psk then attempt user authentication. userLoginSecureExtOrPsk(5) This selects both the userLoginSecureExt and psk modes together such that either is allowed to authorized access. Which mode works for client depends on the client's choice. ext(6) Access to the port is denied until the port client is authenticated (by ext).

h3cDot11SecurityUserLoginTxKeyType.name: h3cDot11SecurityUserLoginTxKeyType
h3cDot11SecurityUserLoginTxKeyType.description: This indicates the key type in the 802.1X EAPOL_Key packet. userLoginTxKeyTypeNone(1) This means the key type is not set yet. userLoginTxKeyTypeDot11Key(2) This selects the 802.11 key type. userLoginTxKeyTypeRsaRC4Key(3) This selects the RC4 key for RSA RC4 session encryption.

h3cDot11SecurityPskKeyMode.name: h3cDot11SecurityPskKeyMode
h3cDot11SecurityPskKeyMode.description: This is the password input mode. When input as pskKeyModePassPhrase, h3cDot11SecurePskKeyString must be 8 to 63 characters; when input as pskKeyModeRawKey, h3cDot11SecurePskKeyString must be 64 characters and each character must be '0'-'9', 'a'-'f' and 'A'-'F'.

h3cDot11SecurityPskKeyString.name: h3cDot11SecurityPskKeyString
h3cDot11SecurityPskKeyString.description: This is the password string used for psk authentication.

h3cDot11WlanMeshIfTable.name: h3cDot11WlanMeshIfTable
h3cDot11WlanMeshIfTable.description: This table is used to configure WLAN mesh interface.

h3cDot11WlanMeshIfEntry.name: h3cDot11WlanMeshIfEntry
h3cDot11WlanMeshIfEntry.description: Each entry contains the WLAN mesh interface configuration.

h3cDot11WlanMeshIfNumber.name: h3cDot11WlanMeshIfNumber
h3cDot11WlanMeshIfNumber.description: This node represents the WLAN mesh interface number.

h3cDot11WlanMeshIfIndex.name: h3cDot11WlanMeshIfIndex
h3cDot11WlanMeshIfIndex.description: This node represents the index of WLAN mesh interface.

h3cDot11WlanMeshRowStatus.name: h3cDot11WlanMeshRowStatus
h3cDot11WlanMeshRowStatus.description: This node represents the WLAN mesh interface row status.

h3cDot11BackupACAdrssIP.name: h3cDot11BackupACAdrssIP
